All Classes

Class Description
Actor
Actor is the base class for all the interactive objects in the Frogger Game.
Each interactive game object is known as an Actor.
Animal
Represents the player's avatar in the game, which is a frog in Frogger Game.
It can move.
AnimalDeath
The base frame class for all kinds of Animal's death.
AnimalDeathContext
This class will refer and execute the action of a type of AnimalDeath .
Strategy Design Pattern is applied here
AnimalDeathTest
Test for AnimalDeathContext, AnimalDeath interface and concrete classes implementing the interface
AnimalTest
Test on Animal class.
BackgroundImage
Represents the background images appeared in the game.
Used in each game level Level, StartScreen, InfoScreen and HighScoreView.
ButtonGenerator
Generator for buttons
CarDeath
Represents a type of Animal Death.
Particularly for when Animal get hit by the Cars/Trucks in the game and die.
Digit
Represents the game points of Animal in Frogger Game.
DryTurtle
Represents the Red Turtle in Frogger Game.
End
Represents the destination Animal should reach to win the game.
There are 3 types of End : an empty End, an End with a coin, an occupied End that has been reached by Animal.
EndTest
Test on End class
GameAction
The base frame class for all kinds of Game Actions in Frogger Game
GameAction_UpLevelTest
Test on GameActionContext, UpLevel class
GameActionContext
This class will refer and execute a type of GameAction
 Strategy Design Pattern is applied here.
HighScoreComparator
Defines how each high score record will be compared.
HighScoreController
HighScoreController can retrieve HighScoreModel information, record the information into file in descending order and update to HighScoreView.
HighScoreModel
Represents the player's high score record which consists of a username and game points.
HighScoreView
Represents how the high score pop up will look like in Frogger Game.
HighScoreViewTest
Test HighScoreView class
ImageGenerator
Generator for images
InfoScreen
Represents the Information Screen of Frogger Game.
Singleton Design Pattern is applied to this class, so there is only one InfoScreen instance throughout the game.
Level
The base class for all game levels.
It is not a ready game level.
Level1
Level 1 of Frogger Game.
Level10
Level 10 of Frogger Game, which is also the final level.
At this level, the game speed is the highest among all the other levels.
Level2
Level 2 of Frogger Game.
Level3
Level 3 of Frogger Game.
At this level, there are coins at some of the End destinations.
Level4
Level 4 of Frogger Game.
Level5
Level 5 of Frogger Game.
Level6
Level 6 of Frogger Game.
At Level 6, there is a Monster appearing in the game, which will eat the player's avatar (the Frog) and minus points.
Level7
Level 7 of Frogger Game.
At this level, all the turtles turn into WetTurtle which will sink into the river from time to time, causing player's avatar to die drowning.
Level8
Level 8 of Frogger Game.
Game settings are similar to Level7 but speeds up and Monster grows bigger.
Level9
Level 9 of Frogger Game.
With coin destinations, Monster, Log-Bomb and all sinking turtles, at Level 9, all game objects are moving even faster than all previous levels.
LevelFactory
This is a Level Factory to create the game levels.
 Factory Method Design Pattern is applied.
LevelFactoryTest
Test LevelFactory class
LevelTest
Test Level superclass and its subclasses
Life
Represents the Life of Animal in Frogger Game.
Log
Represents the logs floating on the river in Frogger Game.
2 types of logs : Log with bombs and Log without bombs.
LogTest
Test Log class
Main
where the whole application is run
MaterialGeneratorTest
Test for the generator classes in froggerMaterialGenerator package
Monster
Represents the Monster in the game.
MonsterDeath
Represents a type of Animal Death.
Particularly for when Animal get eaten by the Monster in the game and die.
Obstacle
Represents the Obstacles, which are the cars and the trucks on the road, in Frogger Game.
Obstacle is also an Actor.
PopHighScore
Represents one of the Game Actions.
Retrieves and Pops the High Score of Frogger Game.
StartScreen
Represents the Start Screen of Frogger Game.
 Singleton Design Pattern is applied to this class, so there is only one StartScreen instance throughout the game.
TextGenerator
Generator for text
Turtle
Represents the turtles in Frogger Game
The base class for Turtle
UpdateLife
Represents one of the Game Actions.
Update the latest amount of Life Animal has.
UpdateScore
Represents one of the Game Actions.
Update the latest scores (via Digit) of Animal.
UpLevel
Represents one of the Game Actions.
Level Up
WaterDeath
Represents a type of Animal Death.
Particularly for when Animal drown into the river and die.
WetTurtle
Represents the Green Turtle in Frogger Game.
World
Represents the game World of Frogger Game where all the game objects are added into this World for gameplay.
